  "description": "Reworking GnoponEmacs as a RITM tool When considering GnoponEmacs as a research tool for Relational Infinity-Topos Modality, I want it to be what lets me, essentially, simulate coKleisli action on my research archive as a relational topology.\nStarting at what\u0026rsquo;s immutable and unique: the :ID: property every Org-roam node has.\nWe\u0026rsquo;re going to start with one node, called \u0026ldquo;node\u0026rdquo; representing what a node at its most general is in this modality, and so it will have a property, :node-relations:, that works like the following:\n",
